<div id="review_36731503" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/36731503" />
    <a title="Will Byrnes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1526851-will-byrnes"><img alt="Will Byrnes" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1291462190p2/1526851.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/36731503?book_show_action=true">Nov 02, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Will Byrnes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Will Byrnes" href="/user/show/1526851-will-byrnes">Will Byrnes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1526851-will-byrnes?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer36731503" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13745098189686136128"><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1521166872i/25220692._SX540_.jpg' width='400' height='xxx' alt='description' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><b>Arturo PÃ©rez-Reverte</b> - image from Periodistadigital.com <br/><br/>Corso is an unscrupulous dealer in and acquirer of rare books. When a famous collector is found dead, he is called in to authenticate what is supposedly an original manuscript chapter of <i>The Three Musketeers</i>. He is subsequently engaged to find the remaining known copies of a mysterious book that may have the power to summon Satan himself. The flap copy portrays this as in intellectual thriller and it is indeed that. It would help to be fami</span>
  <span id="freeText13745098189686136128" style="display:none"><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1521166872i/25220692._SX540_.jpg" width="400" height="xxx" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><b>Arturo PÃ©rez-Reverte</b> - image from Periodistadigital.com <br><br>Corso is an unscrupulous dealer in and acquirer of rare books. When a famous collector is found dead, he is called in to authenticate what is supposedly an original manuscript chapter of <i>The Three Musketeers</i>. He is subsequently engaged to find the remaining known copies of a mysterious book that may have the power to summon Satan himself. The flap copy portrays this as in intellectual thriller and it is indeed that. It would help to be familiar with the work of Dumas, but still fun even in the absence. There are references aplenty that presume an eidetic memory of great literature, or, in the absence of that, at least an eagerness to engage the Google engine to add some light. Whether the refs are obvious or require research, the author makes this a fun-filled journey, a puzzle with literary clues and a surprise ending. Quite recommended. <br><br>PÃ©rez-Reverte is one of the best known, and best-selling contemporary authors of Spanish fiction.<br><br><br>============================<b>EXTRA STUFF&gt;</b><br><br>Links to the authorâs <a target="_blank">personal</a>, <a href="https://twitter.com/perezreverte" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">Twitter</a> and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/perezreverte/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">FB</a> pages</span>
  <a data-text-id="13745098189686136128" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


